Spatial analytics take home assignment¶

June, 2019

Will Geary

Background¶

  • The attached zipped directory contains sea surface chlorophyll-a data [mg m-3] data

  • Data source: MODIS Aqua satellite in the North Atlantic Ocean (10 - 70° N, and 50 - 0° W [-50 - 0° E])

  • Longitudinal degrees are given as negatives

  • Data is collected monthly at 9 km resolution from late 2002 until early 2019

  • There are missing datapoints in every field.

    • Some of these are caused by land
    • Some by a lack of observations

  • Visualizing the data should make it apparent which is which

  • The first column of each CSV gives degrees latitude

  • The first row gives degrees longitude
  • The name of each CSV is structured as follows: ‘chlor_a_yyyyddd’
    • ‘yyyy’ gives the year the observation was taken
    • ‘ddd’ gives the numerical day of the year (0-365)

def year_dayofyear_to_date(year_dayofyear):
    return datetime.datetime.strptime(year_dayofyear, '%Y%j').strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
In [3]:
def zipfile_to_dataframes(zip_path):
    """
    Input: path to uncompressed zipfile containing CSVs
    Output: list of pandas data frames
    """
    print ("Uncompressing and reading data... ")
    zf = zipfile.ZipFile(zip_path)
    csv_files = zf.infolist()
    dates = []
    dataframes = []
    for csv_file in tqdm(csv_files):
        df = pd.read_csv(zf.open(csv_file.filename))
        df.index = df['Unnamed: 0']
        del df['Unnamed: 0']
        df.index.name = 'lat'
        dataframes.append(df)
        year_and_day_of_year = csv_file.filename.split("_")[2].split(".")[0]
        date = year_dayofyear_to_date(year_and_day_of_year)
        dates.append(date)
    return dataframes, dates

Make a GIF over time¶

In [64]:
def save_frames(dataframes, dates, figsize, title, frames_dir="frames", fontsize=26, cmap='Greens', gamma=1./4., color_bar=True, pct_missing=False): 
    if not os.path.exists(frames_dir):
        os.makedirs(frames_dir)
    for df, date in zip(dataframes, dates):
        pct_na = df[df == 999999.000000].count().sum() / (df.shape[0] * df.shape[1])
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)
        plt.imshow(df, cmap, norm=colors.PowerNorm(gamma), vmin=0, vmax=90)
        if color_bar:
            plt.colorbar()
        if pct_missing:
            plt.title(title + " " + date + "\n Percent Missing: " + "{0:.0%}".format(pct_na), fontsize=fontsize);
        else:
            plt.title(title + " " + date, fontsize=fontsize)
        plt.axis('off')
        plt.savefig(os.path.join(frames_dir, date), bbox_inches='tight')
        plt.close()

def make_gif(gif_name, input_dir, output_dir, fps = 5):
    # Gather still frames
    file_list = glob.glob(os.path.join(input_dir, '*.png'))
    clip = mpy.ImageSequenceClip(file_list, fps=fps)
    # Create output folder
    if not os.path.exists(output_dir):
        os.makedirs(output_dir)
    # Write gif
    clip.write_gif(os.path.join(output_dir, '{}.gif'.format(gif_name)), fps=fps)

Plot the mean chlorophyll-a concentration¶

def calc_mean(dataframes):
    
    # Create a dataframe full of zeros
    zeros = dataframes[0].copy()
    zeros.loc[:,:] = 0

    # Sum over each data frame
    for df in dataframes:
        df_ = df.fillna(0)
        zeros += df_

    # Divide by number of data frames
    mean = zeros / len(dataframes)
    return mean

Classify gridded data as water or not water¶

We need to distinguish between coordinates that are on land versus those on water in order to assess trends in missing data.

In [36]:
def water_or_not_water(src, df):
    
    # Create a dataframe full of zeros
    water_values = df.copy()
    water_values.loc[:,:] = 0
    
    lats = list(df.index)
    lons = list(df.columns)

    # Sample the open water raster for each pair of coordinates
    for lat in lats:
        for lon in lons:
            y = float(lat)
            x = float(lon)
            water_val = list(src.sample([(x, y)]))[0]
            water_values.loc[lat, lon] = water_val

    return water_values

Identify missing data (excluding land) at every time step¶

In [57]:
def create_missing_data_frames(dataframes):
    
    df_adjusted_list = []
    
    for dataframe in tqdm(dataframes):

        df_adjusted = dataframe.copy()

        for i in range(len(land_coords_long)):
            this_lon = land_coords_long['variable'].values[i]
            this_lat = land_coords_long['lat'].values[i]
            df_adjusted.loc[this_lat,this_lon] = -1

        df_adjusted = df_adjusted.fillna(999999)
        df_adjusted_list.append(df_adjusted)
        
    return(df_adjusted_list)
